<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Detachment on dasarpAI</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/tags/detachment/</link><description>Recent content in Detachment on dasarpAI</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><managingEditor>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</managingEditor><webMaster>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</webMaster><copyright>© 2026 Dr. Hari Thapliyaal</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://dasarpai.github.io/tags/detachment/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>When Tomorrow Eats Today</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/when-tomorrow-eats-today/</link><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/when-tomorrow-eats-today/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5304-when-tomorrow-eats-today.jpg" alt="When Tomorrow Eats Today" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">&lt;strong>When Tomorrow Eats Today&lt;/strong>
&lt;div id="when-tomorrow-eats-today" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#when-tomorrow-eats-today" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Out of habit, we live in tomorrow.&lt;br>
Out of habit, we live in last year.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;em>We were going to start meditation.&lt;/em>&lt;br>
&lt;em>We were going to read the Gita.&lt;/em>&lt;br>
&lt;em>We were going to fix our temper, our diet, our sleep.&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Out of habit, the sentence never becomes a step.&lt;br>
We polish the plan and call it progress.&lt;br>
We feel busy without moving.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nothing That Came to You Is Yours</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/nothing-that-came-to-you-is-yours/</link><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/nothing-that-came-to-you-is-yours/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5303-nothing-that-came-to-you-is-yours.jpg" alt="Nothing That Came to You Is Yours" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">&lt;strong>Nothing That Came to You Is Yours&lt;/strong>
&lt;div id="nothing-that-came-to-you-is-yours" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#nothing-that-came-to-you-is-yours" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Out of habit, we say &lt;em>my&lt;/em> house, &lt;em>my&lt;/em> son, &lt;em>my&lt;/em> degree.&lt;br>
Out of habit, we count what we earned, saved, and won—&lt;br>
As if breath, body, and mind were made in our workshop.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Out of habit, we forget a simple thing:&lt;br>
What came to you was never yours.&lt;br>
It does not even sit in someone&amp;rsquo;s pocket forever.&lt;br>
It passes through your hands for a while—&lt;br>
Like water in a cup.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>